    {
      "created_at": "2026-06-10T01:59:22.941248",
      "id": "work-1",
      "kind": "statement",
      "label": "Work happens as a graph. A node expresses an intent, and carrying it out grows a graph of further nodes: the steps, the candidates, the checks, the result.",
      "props": {
        "ord": 1,
        "owner": "operator",
        "segment": "work"
      }
    },
    {
      "created_at": "2026-06-10T01:59:23.018847",
      "id": "work-10",
      "kind": "statement",
      "label": "Folding is reflected in both places. The database records the fold, and the filesystem view follows it.",
      "props": {
        "ord": 10,
        "owner": "operator",
        "segment": "work"
      }
    },
    {
      "created_at": "2026-06-10T01:59:23.028759",
      "id": "work-11",
      "kind": "statement",
      "label": "Execution graphs and folding are built in their first form. The operation alphabet is named before its machinery is, so the language exists before the machinery does.",
      "props": {
        "ord": 14,
        "owner": "machine",
        "segment": "work"
      }
    },
    {
      "created_at": "2026-06-10T01:59:22.950534",
      "id": "work-2",
      "kind": "statement",
      "label": "That growing graph is an execution graph. It is a dynamically composed workflow, not a fixed template.",
      "props": {
        "ord": 2,
        "owner": "operator",
        "segment": "work"
      }
    },
    {
      "created_at": "2026-06-10T01:59:22.958907",
      "id": "work-3",
      "kind": "statement",
      "label": "A folder holds one execution graph. The unit on disk is the execution graph, not the single node.",
      "props": {
        "ord": 3,
        "owner": "operator",
        "segment": "work"
      }
    },
    {
      "created_at": "2026-06-10T01:59:22.968081",
      "id": "work-4",
      "kind": "statement",
      "label": "When the work is done, the execution graph folds into the node whose intent spawned it. The result becomes that node's material, and the steps become its history.",
      "props": {
        "ord": 4,
        "owner": "operator",
        "segment": "work"
      }
    },
    {
      "created_at": "2026-06-10T01:59:22.974997",
      "id": "work-5",
      "kind": "statement",
      "label": "Folding preserves relations. A folded graph keeps its nodes and the relations between them, so the history reads as the graph it was, not a flat log.",
      "props": {
        "ord": 5,
        "owner": "operator",
        "segment": "work"
      }
    },
    {
      "created_at": "2026-06-10T01:59:22.983699",
      "id": "work-6",
      "kind": "statement",
      "label": "A folding condition is what makes a graph ready to fold. Its intent is met, or it is abandoned. Until then the graph stays open.",
      "props": {
        "ord": 6,
        "owner": "operator",
        "segment": "work"
      }
    },
    {
      "created_at": "2026-06-10T01:59:22.993648",
      "id": "work-7",
      "kind": "statement",
      "label": "A folding condition is machine-checkable or it spends operator judgment. Which of the two it is must be declared when the graph opens.",
      "props": {
        "ord": 7,
        "owner": "machine",
        "segment": "work"
      }
    },
    {
      "created_at": "2026-06-10T01:59:23.001834",
      "id": "work-8",
      "kind": "statement",
      "label": "Trust in a folded graph comes from the checks at its boundary, not from the competence of whatever ran inside. An unchecked fold is a hope, not a result.",
      "props": {
        "ord": 8,
        "owner": "machine",
        "segment": "work"
      }
    },
    {
      "created_at": "2026-06-10T01:59:23.010057",
      "id": "work-9",
      "kind": "statement",
      "label": "Error compounds through composition. The weaker a graph's checks, the shallower it must stay before folding.",
      "props": {
        "ord": 9,
        "owner": "machine",
        "segment": "work"
      }
    }
  ],
